f.name: POS
f.string: Punctuation (also used for the Sentence Boundary token)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Abbreviation used as an adverb (now obsolete)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Conjunction subordinate (incl. aby, kdyby in all forms)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Abbreviation used as an adjective (now obsolete)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Preposition with attached -ň (pronoun něj, lit. him); proň, naň, .... (POS: P, pronoun)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Relative possessive pronoun jehož, jejíž, ... (lit. whose in subordinate relative clause)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Abbreviation used as a numeral (now obsolete)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Relative/interrogative pronoun with adjectival declension of both types (soft and hard) (jaký, který, čí, ..., lit. what, which, whose, ...)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: The pronoun he in forms requested after any preposition (with prefix n-: něj, něho, ..., lit. him in various cases)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Reflexive pronoun se in long forms (sebe, sobě, sebou, lit. myself / yourself / herself / himself in various cases; se is personless)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Reflexive pronouns se (CASE = 4), si (CASE = 3), plus the same two forms with contracted -s: ses, sis (distinguished by PERSON = 2; also number is singular only)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Possessive reflexive pronoun svůj (lit. my/your/her/his when the possessor is the subject of the sentence)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Relative pronoun jenž, již, ... after a preposition (n-: něhož, niž, ..., lit. who)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Punctuation (except for the virtual sentence boundary word ###, which uses the SUBPOS #)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Abbreviation used as a noun (now obsolete)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Number written using digits (POS: C, numeral)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Adjective, nominal (short, participial) form rád, schopen, ...

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Pronoun, demonstrative (ten, onen, ..., lit. this, that, that ... over there, ...)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Relative pronoun což (corresponding to English which in subordinate clauses referring to a part of the preceding text)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Preposition, part of; never appears isolated, always in a phrase (nehledě (na), vzhledem (k), ..., lit. regardless, because of)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Adjective derived from present transgressive form of a verb

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Personal pronoun, clitical (short) form (mě, mi, ti, mu, ...); these forms are used in the second position in a clause (lit. me, you, her, him), even though some of them (mě) might be regularly used anywhere as well

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Relative pronoun jenž, již, ... not after a preposition (lit. who, whom)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Relative/interrogative pronoun kdo (lit. who), incl. forms with affixes -ž and -s (affixes are distinguished by the category VAR (for -ž) and PERSON (for -s))

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Pronoun, indefinite všechnen, sám (lit. all, alone)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Adjective derived from verbal past transgressive form

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Pronoun svůj, nesvůj, tentam alone (lit. own self, not-in-mood, gone)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Personal pronoun já, ty, on (lit. I, you, he) (incl. forms with the enclitic -s, e.g. tys, lit. you're); gender position is used for third person to distinguish on/ona/ono (lit. he/she/it), and number for all three persons

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Pronoun relative/interrogative co, copak, cožpak (lit. what, isn't-it-true-that)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Pronoun possessive můj, tvůj, jeho (lit. my, your, his); gender position used for third person to distinguish jeho, její, jeho (lit. his, her, its), and number for all three pronouns

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Adjective possessive (with the masculine ending -ův as well as feminine -in)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Preposition (with vocalization -e or -u): (ve, pode, ku, ..., lit. in, under, to)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Pronoun negative (nic, nikdo, nijaký, žádný, ..., lit. nothing, nobody, not-worth-mentioning, no/none)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: (temporary) Word form recognized, but tag is missing in dictionary due to delays in (asynchronous) dictionary creation

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Pronoun relative/interrogative co as an enclitic (after a preposition) (oč, nač, zač, lit. about what, on/onto what, after/for what)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Pronoun indefinite (nějaký, některý, číkoli, cosi, ..., lit. some, some, anybody's, something)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, indefinite (mnoho, málo, tolik, několik, kdovíkolik, ..., lit. much/many, little/few, that much/many, some (number of), who-knows-how-much/many)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Adverb (without a possibility to form negation and degrees of comparison, e.g. pozadu, naplocho, ..., lit. behind, flatly); i.e. both the NEGATION as well as the GRADE attributes in the same tag are marked by - (Not applicable)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Conditional (of the verb být (lit. to be) only) (by, bych, bys, bychom, byste, lit. would)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, generic with adjectival declension ( dvojí, desaterý, ..., lit. two-kinds/..., ten-...)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Adverb (forming negation (NEGATION set to A/N) and degrees of comparison GRADE set to 1/2/3 (comparative/superlative), e.g. velký, za\-jí\-ma\-vý, ..., lit. big, interesting

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, generic; only jedny and nejedny (lit. one-kind/sort-of, not-only-one-kind/sort-of)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, generic greater than or equal to 4 used as a syntactic noun (čtvero, desatero, ..., lit. four-kinds/sorts-of, ten-...)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, generic greater than or equal to 4 used as a syntactic adjective, short form (čtvery, ..., lit. four-kinds/sorts-of)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, cardinal jeden, dva, tři, čtyři, půl, ... (lit. one, two, three, four); also sto and tisíc (lit. hundred, thousand) if noun declension is not used

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Verb, past transgressive; also archaic present transgressive of perfective verbs (ex.: udělav, lit. (he-)having-done; arch. also udělaje (VAR = 4), lit. (he-)having-done)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, cardinal greater than or equal to 5

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, multiplicative indefinite (-krát, lit. (times): mnohokrát, tolikrát, ..., lit. many times, that many times)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Verb, past participle, active (including forms with the enclitic -s, lit. 're (are))

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Verb, past participle, active, with the enclitic -ť, lit. (perhaps) -could-you-imagine-that? or but-because- (both archaic)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, ordinal (adjective declension without degrees of comparison)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Verb, past participle, passive (including forms with the enclitic -s, lit. 're (are))

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Verb, present or future tense, with the enclitic -ť, lit. (perhaps) -could-you-imagine-that? or but-because- (both archaic)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, interrogative kolikrát, lit. how many times?

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, multiplicative, definite (-krát, lit. times: pětkrát, ..., lit. five times)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, indefinite, adjectival declension (nejeden, tolikátý, ..., lit. not-only-one, so-many-times-repeated)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Abbreviation, part of speech unknown/indeterminable (now obsolete)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Numeral, fraction ending at -ina (POS: C, numeral); used as a noun (pětina, lit. one-fifth)

f.name: SUBPOS
f.string: Abbreviation used as a verb (now obsolete)

f.name: GENDER
f.string: Feminine (with singular only) or Neuter (with plural only); used only with participles and nominal forms of adjectives

f.name: GENDER
f.string: Masculine inanimate or Feminine (plural only); used only with participles and nominal forms of adjectives

f.name: GENDER
f.string: Any of the basic four genders

f.name: GENDER
f.string: Not fenimine (i.e., Masculine animate/inanimate or Neuter); only for (some) pronoun forms and certain numerals

f.name: NUMBER
f.string: Singular for feminine gender, plural with neuter; can only appear in participle or nominal adjective form with gender value Q

f.name: VAR
f.string: Not applicable (basic variant, standard contemporary style; also used for standard forms allowed for use in writing by the Czech Standard Orthography Rules despite being marked there as colloquial)

f.name: VAR
f.string: Variant, second most used (less frequent), still standard

f.name: VAR
f.string: Variant, rarely used, bookish, or archaic

f.name: VAR
f.string: Very archaic or bookish, but standard at the time

f.name: VAR
f.string: Colloquial, but (almost) tolerated even in public

f.name: VAR
f.string: Colloquial (standard in spoken Czech), less frequent variant

f.name: VAR
f.string: Special uses, e.g. personal pronouns after prepositions etc.
